<TITLE> Faridpur bus plunge kills 4 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Jan 20 (bdnews24.com)Four people were killed and 20 others injured after a bus lost control and fell into a ditch at Modhukhali in Faridpur on Tuesday, the police said. The accident occurred at around 8 am when the Faridpur-bound bus coming from Alfadanga skidded into the ditch, Modhukhali police chief told bdnews24.com. The dead were identified as Rubel Hossain from Boalmari, Amar Saha from Joy Nagar, Sufia Begum from Sotashi village and Selina Begum from Alfadanga upazila. The police and fire fighters rushed to the spot. They handed over the dead bodies to their families and sent the injured people to the hospitals, the officer said. The bus driver and his helper were nowhere to be seen. b
